* ============================================================================
* TICKET B — PHASE 0 decode-cost benchmark (AIF-043 gate)  v5 — self-timing
* ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Now self-times via SET TIMER (fixed 2026-07-22 to fire in script/DO mode) and
* cross-checks with SECONDS() (fixed to sub-second/ms resolution). Each measured
* command prints its own "ELAPSED : <sec> s" line; the SECONDS() brackets are a
* redundant cross-check. Read-only, no mutation, no tuple-core touch.
*
* Compare:
*   SUM  GPA                          -> decode 1 numeric + aggregate
*   DEC1 COUNT FOR GPA>=0             -> decode 1 numeric + compare
*   DEC3 COUNT FOR GPA>=0 .AND. SID>=0 .AND. MAJOR<="ZZZZ" -> decode 3 fields
*
* decode adds (DEC3 - DEC1) for 2 extra field decodes. If DEC3 ~= DEC1 (adding
* field decode barely moves the time), the scan is NOT decode-bound => Option B
* KILL. If DEC3 >> DEC1, decode is a real slice => candidate GO.
* (Phase-0 already ran: DEC1 ~39s, DEC3 ~92s over 1M rows => evaluator-bound,
*  Option B KILLED. This script now self-times for the scan-evaluator lane.)
* ============================================================================
SET ECHO OFF
STOP_ON_ERROR OFF

SET PATH DBF DBF/pinocchio
SET PATH INDEXES INDEXES/pinocchio
SET PATH LMDB LMDB/pinocchio

USE STUDENTS
SET ORDER TO 0
COUNT

ECHO === WARM (prime cache; ignore) ===
COUNT FOR GPA >= 0

* Timer is toggled ON only around each measured command so the ELAPSED block is
* clean. The SECONDS() brackets (printed with the timer OFF) are the redundant
* cross-check; subtract the pair for the same elapsed the ELAPSED line reports.

ECHO === SUM GPA (1-field decode + accumulate, no predicate) ===
? SECONDS()
SET TIMER ON
SUM GPA
SET TIMER OFF
? SECONDS()

ECHO === DEC1 COUNT FOR GPA >= 0  (+ 1 predicate term) ===
? SECONDS()
SET TIMER ON
COUNT FOR GPA >= 0
SET TIMER OFF
? SECONDS()

ECHO === DEC3 COUNT FOR GPA >= 0 .AND. SID >= 0 .AND. MAJOR <= "ZZZZ"  (3 terms) ===
? SECONDS()
SET TIMER ON
COUNT FOR GPA >= 0 .AND. SID >= 0 .AND. MAJOR <= "ZZZZ"
SET TIMER OFF
? SECONDS()

ECHO ============================================================================
ECHO Read the "ELAPSED : <sec> s" line printed after each measured command.
ECHO Self-timed baseline floor (2026-07-22, steady_clock, cross-checked by SECONDS):
ECHO   Host: Alienware m16 R2, Core Ultra 9 185H, 64 GB, D:=Samsung 970 EVO NVMe.
ECHO   (canonical: PINOCCHIO_STRESS_TEST_PLAN_V1.md / PINOCCHIO_MACHINE_PROFILE_CURRENT_V1.json)
ECHO   SUM GPA  ~19.5 s | DEC1 ~38.5 s | DEC3 ~70.5 s  over 1,000,000 rows.
ECHO   predicate machinery over bare aggregate = DEC1 - SUM ~19 s/1M (~19 us/row).
ECHO   marginal per predicate term = (DEC3 - DEC1)/2 ~16 s/1M (~16 us/row).
ECHO decode-bound if DEC3 - DEC1 is a large share of DEC1; else Option B = KILL.
ECHO ============================================================================
